FlexCards Versioning

FlexCards supports versioning. You can create an identical copy of a FlexCard by creating a new version and keeping other versions with the same name, but with a new version number.

The name, author, and version combination must be unique for each component in an org. Only one version of a component can be active at a time.

When you create a new version of a FlexCard, the version number increases by 1 and the Status is inactive.

The following fields are involved in the versioning process:

* Name: specifies the name of the FlexCard
* Author: specifies the user organization that created the FlexCard
* Version: an integer that increases by one with every new version
* Active: indicates whether a record is active for runtime use

Create a New Version of a FlexCard
You can create a new version of a FlexCard in the FlexCard Designer when you want to make slight modifications to a current FlexCard. Creating a version makes an exact copy with a version number equal to the latest version number plus one.

FIELD DESCRIPTION

* Name: specifies the name of the FlexCard
* Author: specifies the user organization that created the FlexCard
* Version: an integer that increases by one with every new version
* Active: indicates whether a record is active for runtime use
